headline: Is It Time To Reconsider JPMorgan Chase (JPM) After Recent Share Price Weakness?
summary: If you are wondering whether JPMorgan Chase is still fairly priced or offering value at current levels, this article will walk through what the numbers are actually saying about the stock. The share price last closed at US$297.67, with returns of a 1.6% decline over 7 days, roughly flat over 30 days, an 8.5% decline year to date, and a 16.2% return over the past year. All of these figures provide useful context before comparing that price to estimated value. Recent headlines around JPMorgan...

headline: Dimon Says JPMorgan's Rivals Are Doing 'Dumb Things'
summary: JPMorgan CEO Jamie Dimon, when asked about fierce competition across the financial industry, said he's starting to see parallels to the era before the 2008 financial crisis, when a rush to make loans ended disastrously. "I see a couple people doing some dumb things," Dimon told investors on Monday. Bloomberg's Silas Brown reports.
